The paper deals with improving the complexity of an algorithm for solving parity games, which is a topic in theoretical computer science related to algorithms and complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves some aspects of logic and computation (cs.LO), computational geometry (cs.CG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and game theory (cs.GT), which are all relevant sub-categories.
